<!doctype html>

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>Goal Patrol - Help</title>
    <link href="/css/bootstrap.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="/css/bootstrap-theme.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="css/GoalPatrol.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <script src="js/angular.1.2.26.min.js"></script>
    <script src="js/jquery-1.11.2.min.js"></script>
    <script src="js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
    <script src="js/GoalPatrolScript.js"></script>
    <script>
      $(function() {
        //Randomly choose patial
        var randomPartial = $('#getPartial').attr('name');
        if(randomPartial == 1) {
          $('#originalPartial').css('display','block');
        }
        else {
          $('#newPartial').css('display', 'block');
        }
      });
    </script>
  </head>

  <body>

    <!-- Header: Title & Name -->
    <div class="header-container container">
      <div name="{{partial}}" id="getPartial" style="display: none"></div>
      <span id="originalPartial" style="display: none;">
        {{> headerOriginal}}
      </span>
      <span id="newPartial" style="display: none;">
        {{> header}}
      </span>
      <div id="mobile-name" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-top: 15px; margin-left: 8px; display: none">
      Hi, {{#users}}{{name}}{{/users}}
      </div>
    </div>

    <br> <!--Extra spacing-->
    <br>

    <div class= "container">
      <h1 align="center">Help/Tutorial</h1>
      <h3 style="display: inline-block">Don't need help? Send a goal to someone now. &nbsp; &nbsp;</h3>
      <button class="btn btn-warning" onclick="window.location.href='/sendgoal'" style="width: 150px">Send Goal</button>
      <br>
      <h3 style="display: inline-block">Don't want to do that now? &nbsp; &nbsp;</h3>
      <button class="btn btn-info" onclick="window.location.href='/'" style="width: 150px">Go Home</button>
      <br><br>
      <ol>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <li>Connect with friends by searching for their emails.</li>
        <li>Set a goal for your friend and wait to receive a goal from your friend, or if you've already received a goal from a friend, you can either accept or decline the goal.</li>
        <li>Upon accepting the goal, set up a specific plan for achieving this goal (i.e. how many hours you will spend for a certain number of days per week).</li>
        <li>Record your progress by rating the goal (difficulty, experience, and preference) as you work towards achieving your goal.</li>
        <li>At the end of the week, discuss the goals with your goal patrol buddy, using the progress you've recorded as a reference. </li>
      </ol>
      <h2>Tips</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>You can integrate your Google calendar when planning your goals! </li>
          <li>Try to keep the goals you set for your friends as specific as possible so that they can work out a plan for achieving the goal by setting the number of hours they will spend as well as the days they will pick to work on the goal.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

  </body>

</html>
